               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Sinodos (fols. 1ra-166vb)
 I-1) Statutes or Commandments
                     (tǝʾǝzazat) of the Apostles (fols. 1ra-34vb, 164ra-166vb)
 I-2) Apostolic
                     Canons: 54 canons (fols. 35ra-42va)
 I-3) Canons after the Ascension of Our
                     Lord (fols. 43ra-47vb)
 I-4) Apostolic Canons: 81 ʾabṭǝlisat (n°1) (fols.
                     47vb-56rb)
 I-5) Canons of Simon the Canaanite (n°2) (fols. 56rb-63ra)
                     I-6) Apostolic Canons: 81 canons (fols. 63ra-66vb)
 I-7) Apostolic Canons:
                     81 ʾabṭǝlisat (n°2) (fols. 66vb-74vb)
 I-8) Canons of Simon the Canaanite
                     (n°1) (fols. 75ra-81va)
 I-9) Melkite Index (fols. 81va-82rb)
 I-10)
                     Canons of the Council of Ancyra (fols. 82rb-85vb)
 I-11) Canons of the
                     Council of Neocaesarea (fols. 85vb-87vb)
 I-12) Canons of the Council of
                     Gangra (fols. 87vb-89rb)
 I-13) Canons of the Council of Sardica (fols.
                     89rb-91rb)
 I-14) Canons of the Council of Antioch (fols. 91va-95vb)
                     I-15) Canons of the Council of Laodicea (fols. 95vb-102rb)
 I-16) Canons of
                     the Council of Nicaea (20) (fols. 102va-106va) 
 I-17) Canons of the
                     Council of Nicaea (84) (fols. 106va-116vb)
 I-18) Discourse of the 318
                     Nicene Fathers on the Right Faith and on the Monastic Life (fols.
                     117ra-119rb)
 I-19) Letter of Peter to Clement (fols. 119rb-122vb)
                     I-20) Interpretation of the Ten Commandments by John Chrysostom (fols.
                     122vb-128vb)
 I-21) Exposition and admonition on the role of Our Lord in
                     our salvation (also called On the Essence of the Holy Trinity) (fols.
                     128vb-130va) 
 I-22) Exposition and admonition on the way of virtue and
                     perdition (also called How to Distinguish between God and Evil) (fols.
                     130va-131rb) 
 I-23) Exposition and admonition on the fear of God (fols.
                     131rb-135ra)
 I-24) Exposition and admonition on not associating with Jews
                     (also called On the Former People of God) (fols. 135ra-142rb) 
 I-25)
                     Exposition and admonition of Gregory of Armenia against the Jews (fols.
                     142rb-146rb)
 I-26) Exposition and admonition to believers on wise conduct
                     (fols. 146va-155rb)
 I-27) Penitential canons given to St Peter (fols.
                     155rb-160vb)
 I-28) Index of the Statutes or Commandments (tǝʾǝzazat) of
                     the Apostles (fols. 161va-162vb)
 
 Additio 1; colophon.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">

                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                     <colophon xml:id="coloph1">
                        <locus target="#161vb">161vb</locus>: ተፈጸመ፡ በዝየሲኖዶስ፡ ስረዩ፡ ሊተ፡ ወባርኩኒ፡ ዘጸሐፎ፡
                        ወለዘአጽሐፎ፡ ንቡረ፡ ይምሐሮሙ፡ በምንግ&lt;ሥ&gt;ተ፡ ሰማት[sic]። በስመ፡ ሥሉስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ወሀብክዋ፡ ለዛቲ፡ ሲኖዶስ፡
                        አነ፡ ስምዖን፡ ቄሰ፡ ገበዝ፡ ለዛቲ፡ ቤተ፡ ክርስቲያን፡ ቤተ፡ ሐ[ዋርያት?]፡ ወሀብክዋ፡ ለ፲ወ፪፡ ሐዋርያት… Written
                        in a secondary hand, partly readable. The note states that Sǝmʿon, qesa gabaz
                        of the church Beta Ḥawāryāt, donated the book to the church of the 12 Apostles.
                     </colophon>
                  </msItem>
                  
               </msContents>
               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="Codex">
                     <supportDesc>
                        <support>
                           <material key="parchment"/>
                        </support>
                        <extent>Made of <measure unit="leaf">165.0</measure> folios, of which
                              <measure unit="leaf" type="blank"/> blank <locus target="#161r">161r</locus>, 163r-v., in <measure unit="quire"/> quires (Due to the
                           condition of the Ms., the structure of the quires cannot be
                           established.). <dimensions type="outer">
                              <height unit="mm">360</height>
                              <width unit="mm">260</width>
                              <depth unit="mm">110</depth>
                           </dimensions>
                        </extent>
                        <foliation/>
                        <collation>
                           <list>
                              <item xml:id="q1">Due to the condition of the Ms., the structure of
                                 the quires cannot be established.</item>
                           </list>
                        </collation>
                        <condition key="deficient">The Ms. is worn. 
 The boards and leaves are
                           heavily affected by humidity and mould. The board attachment, sewing are
                           damaged. The last three fols. are misplaced: <locus from="164" to="165">164-165</locus> should have been placed between fols. 1 and 2.
                           Some fols. are heavily damaged, e.g. fols. 1, 161,165,166.
 Some
                           fols. are damaged by water, e.g. fols. 1-9, 149-160.
 Tears carefully
                           amended on <locus target="#74">74</locus>, 95, 100, 156.</condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout columns="2" writtenLines="36">
                           <dimensions unit="mm">
                              <height>267</height>
                              <width>200</width>
                              <dim type="intercolumn">15</dim>
                           </dimensions>
                           <dimensions type="margin">
                              <dim type="top">35</dim>
                              <dim type="bottom">53</dim>
                              <dim type="right">40</dim>
                              <dim type="left">13</dim>
                              <dim type="intercolumn">15</dim>
                           </dimensions>
                           <note>All data for <locus target="#2r">2r</locus>.</note>
                           <ab type="ruling"/>
                           <ab type="pricking">Pricking is mostly visible; ruling is partly visible. </ab>
                           <ab type="ruling" subtype="pattern"> Ruling pattern:
                              1A-1A-1A1A/0-0/0-0/C. </ab>
                           <ab type="pricking"> Primary pricks are visible. </ab>
                           <ab type="pricking"> Ruling pricks are partly visible. </ab>
                           <ab type="ruling"> The upper line is usually written above the ruling
                              (frequently also below the ruling, cp. <locus from="96" to="99">96-99</locus>, 108-111, 115, 116, etc.)</ab>
                           <ab type="ruling"> The bottom line is written above the ruling.</ab>
                           <ab type="ruling"> A few bottom ruling lines are not used in some fols.,
                              e.g. <locus target="#4r">4r</locus>.</ab>
                           <ab type="ruling"> The columns (and margins) are frequently of irregular
                              size; the scribes (esp. hand a) frequently disregarded the ruling;
                              columns are frequently of somewhat irregular size.</ab>
                        </layout>
                        <layout/>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Hand a: poor. Hands b, c: careful.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red.</seg>
                        <date>Late 15th - mid-16th century (?)</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Incipit of Text I and its sections; number, title
                           and incipit of canons; elements of the punctuation signs; Ethiopic
                           numerals.
 On the incipit page of Text I and of its sections, a few
                           lines are rubricated (alternating with black lines).</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">Hand a: <locus from="1ra" to="30vb">1ra-30vb</locus>, 32ra-33vb, 35ra-42va,
                        164ra-165vb.</handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic"> Hand b: <locus from="43ra" to="162vb">43ra-162vb</locus>.</handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h4" script="Ethiopic"> Hand c: <locus target="#31r">31r-</locus>v, 34r-v, 42vb. Hand c corrected and made addition to Text
                        I-1 and I-2 written in hand a: e.g. on <locus target="#41va">41va</locus>,
                        41vb,
                        42vb.</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#33va">f. 33va</locus>
                           <desc>: Record concerning a land grant (?).</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note> Written in a more recent hand, 17th or 18th cent. (?) </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The title ሲኖዶስ is written on the front board.
 - Use
                           of compressed script: <locus target="#31rv">31rv</locus>, 34rv, 42vb,
                           116rb-117vb.
 - The text is written over extensive erasure: <locus target="#40v">40v</locus>, 42vb (canon of the biblical books?).
 -
                           Cues for the rubricator (numerals, written sometimes in tiny size and
                           thin strokes, but sometimes in regular size): <locus from="63" to="66va">63-66va</locus>, 95v, 159r-160r.
 - Small crosses mostly of
                           simple form, sometimes of sophisticated form, or tiny lines separating
                           the words, might indicate the process of correction or preparation for
                           inserting text dividers: <locus target="#139v">139v</locus>, 140r,
                           147v.
 - Some parchment leaves are produced rather crudely.</item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- A piece of thread is inserted in the upper corner
                              of <locus target="#96">fol. 96</locus>.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding contemporary="partly">
                        <decoNote xml:id="b1">Two thick wooden boards.
 Two pairs of sewing
                           stations.</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b2" type="bindingMaterial">
                           <material key="wood"/>
                        </decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b3" type="Endbands"/>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b4" type="Other">Small holes are visible in the centre
                           fold of the quires (e.g. <locus from="86v" to="87r">86v-87r</locus>), one
                           close to the head, one close to the tail.</decoNote>
                        <decoNote xml:id="b5">None.</decoNote>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
